SIMPLE: smoke_out
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Smoke out
<hw>Smoke` out"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To drive from a
refuge or hiding place by causing dense smoke or other noxious fumes to
permeate the refuge; <as>as, the police <ex>smoked out</ex> the bank
robbers with tear gas</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <mark>[metaphorical]</mark>
<def>To expose; to force into public view; to reveal in its true light;
<as>as, the reporter <ex>smoked out</ex> the waffling candidate with a
direct question, exposing his view on the issue</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Smoker</ent>⟦br⟧
